tool_description:
The Cat Breeds API provides comprehensive data on various cat breeds sourced from Wikipedia pages. 

Users can access detailed information about cat breeds, their origins, characteristics, and images.

The API's rich dataset and intuitive endpoints empower developers to access comprehensive information about various cats efficiently.

Whether for research, educational purposes, or cat enthusiasts, the Cat Breeds API offers valuable insights into the diverse world of feline companions.

title: Cat breeds

api_list.name: Group breed data by property
api_list.description: This endpoint will group the available data by the given property and the property value. The property can be any property of the JSON response object including the properties of the meta object.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://cat-breeds.p.rapidapi.com/cat_breeds/group/origin/united states"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "cat-breeds.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
